# Component Rules

## Structure
- One component per file
- Props type defined above the component in the same file
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging
- Apply design tokens from `@/lib/design-tokens.ts`

## Shadcn UI
- Always use Shadcn components from `@/components/ui/`
- Customize via Tailwind classes, NOT by modifying Shadcn source
- Use `Form` component with `react-hook-form` + Zod for all forms

## Server vs Client
- Pages and layouts: Server Components
- Interactive elements (forms, dropdowns, modals): Client Components with `"use client"`
- Data fetching: Server Components or Server Actions only
- Never use `useEffect` for data fetching

## Accessibility
- All interactive elements must have `aria-label` or visible labels
- Use semantic HTML (`nav`, `main`, `section`, `article`)
- Keyboard navigation support for custom components
- Focus management in modals and dialogs

## Mobile-First
- All components must be responsive
- Start with mobile styles, add `md:` and `lg:` breakpoints
- Touch targets minimum 44x44px
- Use `Sheet` component for mobile navigation
